title: fatal: ambiguous argument 'HEAD': unknown revision or path not in the working tree.
body:
Trying to replicate the [titanic example](https://uber.github.io/ludwig/examples/#kaggles-titanic-predicting-survivors)

```
ludwig experiment \
  --data_csv data/titanic_train.csv \
  --model_definition_file model_definition.yaml
```

Getting this error message

```
_         _        _
| |_  _ __| |_ __ _(_)__ _
| | || / _` \ V  V / / _` |
|_|\_,_\__,_|\_/\_/|_\__, |
                     |___/
ludwig v0.1.0 - Experiment

fatal: ambiguous argument 'HEAD': unknown revision or path not in the working tree.
Use '--' to separate paths from revisions, like this:
'git <command> [<revision>...] -- [<file>...]'
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/bin/ludwig", line 11, in <module>
    sys.exit(main())
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ludwig/cli.py", line 86, in main
    CLI()
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ludwig/cli.py", line 64, in __init__
    getattr(self, args.command)()
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ludwig/cli.py", line 67, in experiment
    experiment.cli(sys.argv[2:])
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ludwig/experiment.py", line 548, in cli
    experiment(**vars(args))
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ludwig/experiment.py", line 201, in experiment
    random_seed
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/site-packages/ludwig/utils/misc.py", line 50, in get_experiment_description
    subprocess.check_output(['git', 'rev-parse', 'HEAD']).decode(
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/subprocess.py", line 356, in check_output
    **kwargs).stdout
  File "/Users/adhiman/anaconda3/lib/python3.6/subprocess.py", line 438, in run
    output=stdout, stderr=stderr)
subprocess.CalledProcessError: Command '['git', 'rev-parse', 'HEAD']' returned non-zero exit status 128.
```
